.TH "TCC-PREAPPROVE" "1" "Jul 08, 2026" "0.0.3" "tccx"
.SH NAME
tcc-preapprove \- pre-approve macOS TCC permissions
.sp
A Swift package built on \X'tty: link https://github.com/apple/swift-argument-parser'\fI\%swift\-argument\-parser\fP\X'tty: link', providing four subcommands with real
\fB\-\-help\fP, validation, and routing.
.sp
Built from the \fBtccd\fP (macOS 10.15.6) reverse\-engineering notes in these docs. For \fIwhy\fP the
direct\-DB paths need SIP disabled, see \fI\%TCC Internals & Pre\-Approval (macOS 10.15.6 tccd)\fP and the synthesis \fI\%SIP × TCC\fP\&.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.IP "Note"
.sp
\fBlist\fP and \fBprofile\fP work with no special privilege. The direct\-DB write paths (\fBgrant\fP,
\fBrevoke\fP) can build a genuine grant row but can only \fBpersist\fP it with \fBSIP filesystem
protection disabled\fP (\fBCSR_ALLOW_UNRESTRICTED_FS\fP) \- \fBTCC.db\fP lives in a SIP
storage\-class\-protected directory only \fBtccd\fP is entitled to write. The only persist path
needing no SIP change is the sanctioned \fBMDM/PPPC profile\fP (\fBprofile\fP subcommand).
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH BUILD & RUN (MACOS)
.sp
From the repository root:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
yarn build                  # or: swift build
swift run tcc\-preapprove \-\-help

# run a subcommand directly:
swift run tcc\-preapprove list \-\-client com.googlecode.iterm2
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
