.SH SERVICE ALIASES
.sp
\fBdownloads\fP, \fBdocuments\fP, \fBdesktop\fP, \fBfda\fP/\fBfulldisk\fP, \fBaccessibility\fP,
\fBremovable\fP, \fBnetwork\fP, \fBappbundles\fP, \fBdeveloperfiles\fP \- or pass a raw \fBkTCCService…\fP
name.
.SH NOTES
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
Direct\-DB subcommands need Full Disk Access or SIP disabled (see \fI\%SIP × TCC\fP and
\fI\%SIP filesystem protection (\(dqrootless\(dq)\fP). On macOS 11+ this effectively means SIP off.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBprofile\fP output should be \fBsigned\fP before MDM distribution:
\fBsecurity cms \-S \-N \(dq<cert>\(dq \-i tcc.mobileconfig \-o signed.mobileconfig\fP, and PPPC only takes
effect under user\-approved MDM / supervision.
.IP \(bu 2
A grant written with SIP off stays valid after re\-enabling SIP \- the row is checked against the
running client\(aqs code requirement, not SIP state.
